    "narrative": "The Austin Waves head into today\u2019s slate with a potent lineup anchored by **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (75.66) and **Gunnar Henderson** (75.34). While **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** faces a respectable arm in Woods Richardson, his elite xwOBA remains the safest floor in our current build. **Gunnar Henderson** offers the highest upside of the day, benefiting significantly from his leadoff position and a favorable platoon advantage against Warren. The most explosive matchup, however, belongs to **Josh Lowe** (72.21), who draws Christian Scott and his inflated 15.44 xERA. Though his lineup position is currently pending, the confluence of a massive SP weakness and a positive platoon adjustment makes him a locked-in starter. **Drake Baldwin** also earns a high mark (72.68) today, as his favorable park factors and the poor efficiency of Quintana provide an ideal environment for him to generate production from the #2 spot.\n\nThe most difficult decision on today\u2019s board centered on the utility spot, where **Nolan Schanuel** (64.63) just narrowly edged out **Josh Jung** (58.11). While **Josh Jung** has shown recent flashes, the raw projection favored **Nolan Schanuel**\u2019s matchup against Scott. We are also monitoring the SB-heavy profile of **Heliot Ramos** (60.35); despite a challenging matchup against McClanahan, his elite sprint speed and the opponent's slow delivery to the plate keep him in the lineup, as we continue to over-index on stolen base potential to maintain our edge in that category. Note that we are operating under \"Lineup Pending\" assumptions for **Miguel Vargas**, **Josh Lowe**, and **Nolan Schanuel**; any shifts in the batting order could necessitate a re-evaluation of our efficiency scores before first pitch. We are currently sitting **Marcell Ozuna** (55.76) and **Brady House** (44.20) on the bench, as their lack of platoon or park advantages today failed to provide the necessary ceiling to displace our current starters.",
